Comment:
Just went to go see it in theaters, and I'd advise against watching it. Personally, I thought it was boring, the plot was rushed, the characters were poorly introduced, and anything that happened that brought up questions never reoccurred in the movie, an example;

[Spoiler Alert]

At one point a swarm of bee's go around Mila Kunis and she is able to control them, and it never again is spoken of, or thoroughly explained throughout the movie.

[Spoiler Done]

I expected a great science fiction movie, like Star Wars or something like that, but what I ended up with was Eddie Redmayne as a quiet psychopath bent on killing his mother's reincarnation.

And Romance, there was too much romance in the film to the point where you would want to end your life after 45 minutes.

However the visuals were stunning, I must admit that. And the theme was interesting but they didn't do it right.

This movie had potential but they failed at it. I give this movie a 5/10. I'd advise NOT to see it.
